        "can_see_hidden_post": false,
        "can_unaccept_answer": false,
        "can_view_edit_history": true,
        "can_wiki": false,
        "cooked": "<p>To be clear, this is also supported in OpenSCAD.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In addition to the installed fonts ( for windows only fonts installed as admin for all users ), it\u2019s possible to add project specific font files. Supported font file formats are <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TrueType\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">TrueType</a> Fonts (<em>.ttf) and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenType\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">OpenType</a> Fonts (</em>.otf). The files need to be registered with use&lt;&gt;.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\"> use &lt;ttf/paratype-serif/PTF55F.ttf&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>It seems relatively simple to expand the allowed uploaded files to include <code>.ttf</code> and <code>.otf</code> file types, which would allow developers (and users) to add custom fonts for their parametric models.</p>",
        "created_at": "2025-03-20T19:00:05.821Z",
